    <briefdescription>
<para>The <computeroutput><ref refid="classCGAL_1_1Polygon__vertical__decomposition__2" kindref="compound">Polygon_vertical_decomposition_2</ref></computeroutput> class implements a convex decompistion of a polygon or a polygon with holes into pseudo trapezoids utilizing the <ref refid="group__PkgArrangement2Funcs_1gae20b2917f6de15db9bf025f83abf8e89" kindref="member" external="/home/cgal-testsuite/cgal_doc_build/CGAL-4.13-I-128/doc/scripts/build_doc/doc_tags/Arrangement_on_surface_2.tag">CGAL::decompose()</ref> free function of the <ref refid="index_1chapterArrangement_on_surface_2" kindref="member" external="/home/cgal-testsuite/cgal_doc_build/CGAL-4.13-I-128/doc/scripts/build_doc/doc_tags/Arrangement_on_surface_2.tag">2D Arrangements</ref> package. </para>    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The algorithm operates in <formula id="12">$ O(n \log n)$</formula> time and takes <formula id="13">$ O(n)$</formula> space at the worst case, where <formula id="14">$ n$</formula> is the size of the input polygon.</para><para><xrefsect id="models_1_models000006"><xreftitle>Is Model Of</xreftitle><xrefdescription><para><computeroutput><ref refid="classPolygonWithHolesConvexDecomposition__2" kindref="compound">PolygonWithHolesConvexDecomposition_2</ref></computeroutput></para></xrefdescription></xrefsect></para>    </detaileddescription>
